        srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Midway-Deck.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=267&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=28f74e7e7763022943c754df82400be9 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Midway-Deck.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=533&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=9e066facdadbb53c00e9566bf0baa736 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Midway-Deck.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=800&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=f4d28d3587595aef39d225ad11c5f408 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Midway-Deck.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=867&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=e9ec1652291f3ca789386c26284d459b 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Midway-Deck.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=967&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=d0c837217e30b4f399243f9006652026 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Midway-Deck.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1067&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=0c2ac5755b5f570dff4cc648454f3b2a 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Midway-Deck.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1334&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=27b0d839d615041f286f988fb897df26 2000w"
                    />

            
    
<figcaption class="attribution">
        <span class="attribution__caption">Bohemians, as the club’s members call themselves, mingle on the deck of Midway camp.</span>
    
        <span class="attribution__credit">
        <span class="a11y">Credit: </span>
        Obtained by ProPublica
    </span>
    
    
    </figcaption>

</figure>

        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="77.0">During the annual retreats, the Kochs often discussed political strategy with fellow guests, according to multiple people who’ve spent time with them at Midway. A few years ago, Brian Hooks, one of the leaders of their political network, was a guest at the camp the same weekend Thomas was there. A former Midway employee recalled the brothers discussing super PAC spending during the Obama years and complaining about government regulation.</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="78.0">“Chevron was one of the big things the Koch brothers were interested in,” the former employee said. He did not remember if Thomas was present for any of the discussions of the doctrine.</p>
        
    
