            <div class="story-promo__info" dir="auto">
                <strong class="story-promo__hed">Clarence Thomas and the Billionaire</strong>
                            </div>
        </a>

    
</aside>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="80.0">But Thomas and the Kochs developed a bond over their years at the retreat, according to five people who spent time with them there. They discussed politics, business and their families. They often sat together at meals and sat up talking at night at the lodge. A photo obtained by ProPublica captures Thomas and David Koch smiling on Midway’s deck. David’s windbreaker features an owl insignia, the symbol of the club.</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="81.0">One tradition at Midway is a lecture series, often held beneath the redwoods on the camp’s deck. The weekend Thomas was there in July 2016, the Midway schedule featured a talk from Henry Kissinger and another by Michael Bloomberg and Arthur Brooks, then president of the conservative think tank the American Enterprise Institute. Over breakfast Friday morning, the author Bjorn Lomborg delivered a lecture on climate change. Lomborg has for years argued the threat of global warming is overstated, saying that rising temperatures will actually save lives.</p>
        
    
                    

<figure
    data-pp-id="82"
    data-pp-blocktype="image"
    class="bb-image size10 center  wide-sm wrap 
                ">

    


                    
    


    <img
        class=""
        alt=""
        width="1899"
        height="1266"
        loading="lazy" js-autosizes        src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Calendar.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=533&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=5e7a20d9018aa8f8ea9ffab842203541"
        srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Calendar.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=267&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=98b8a86d09a56ccc3d2b6a48d340ea3b 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Calendar.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=533&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=5e7a20d9018aa8f8ea9ffab842203541 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Calendar.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=800&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=3415bf253d84ddcc4d9590c3853ecbe3 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Calendar.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=867&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=7f95d1e6f3aac6ce30519f2188c449a0 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Calendar.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=967&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=921dc0dcd6ab8dff846db2c94c1697f7 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Calendar.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1067&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=0cb72c3f82a04bc891ff20aa3eecd6fa 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20230920-Calendar.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1333&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=55d7abdfbaa11ed183e4f365eb5db90b 2000w"
                    />

            
    
<figcaption class="attribution">
        <span class="attribution__caption">A Midway schedule featured a talk by Thomas and other events.</span>
    
        <span class="attribution__credit">
        <span class="a11y">Credit: </span>
        Highlighting by ProPublica. Obtained by ProPublica.
    </span>
    
    
    </figcaption>

</figure>

        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="83.0">Thomas spoke that year as well. He talked about his friend Justice Scalia, who had recently died, according to a person who attended. Scalia, a conservative luminary, had been a prominent advocate for the Chevron doctrine, but Thomas said he believed his colleague was coming around to Thomas’ revised view on it before his death.</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="84.0">Thomas didn’t explain what he meant by that. “It was an aside,” the person said, “like he assumed most of the people in the room knew his position.”</p>
        
    
                    <div class="article-body__bottom-notes" data-pp-location="bottom-note">
                                    

                                    
        <div class="article-body__note article-body__note--tips-callout" data-pp-location="bottom-note" data-pp-view data-pp-category="get involved">
                        <p>Do you have any tips on the Supreme Court? Josh Kaplan can be reached by email at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#f3999c809b8692dd9892839f929db383819c8386919f9a9092dd9c8194"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="cea4a1bda6bbafe0a5afbea2afa08ebebca1bebbaca2a7adafe0a1bca9">[email&#160;protected]</span></a> and by Signal or WhatsApp at 734-834-9383. Justin Elliott can be reached by email at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#a6ccd3d5d2cfc8e6d6d4c9d6d3c4cacfc5c788c9d4c1"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="ec86999f988582ac9c9e839c998e80858f8dc2839e8b">[email&#160;protected]</span></a> or by Signal or WhatsApp at 774-826-6240.</p>

        </div>

    
